//axhoc_completion
Successful execution mirrors all tool images into the reliquary namespace.
Set `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«RELIQUARY»` in vessel {rbrv_regime} files to use this reliquary for subsequent conjure operations.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_retriever_roster}

NOTE: This operation rosters
{rbtr_retriever}
{giam_service_account_s}
in the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
via per-SA fact-file emission.
Read-only observation: lists all service accounts, filters to retriever-prefixed emails, and emits one fact per discovered SA via
{buf_write_fact_multi}
against the `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_retriever` extension constant.
Fact value is the full SA email; `file_root` is the bare identity extracted from the email.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *List Service Accounts*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/list[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ACCOUNTS»` from response `.accounts[]` array

//axhos_step
. *Filter to
{rbtr_retriever}
Service Accounts*:
.. From `«ACCOUNTS»`, read the `.email` field of each entry and test whether it matches `^${RBCC_account_retriever}-(.+)@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}$`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_EMAILS»` — the matching emails; per-role observation per BBAAQ contract

//axhos_step
. *Emit Fact Per Discovered
{rbtr_retriever}*:
.. For each `«SA_EMAIL»` in `«RETRIEVER_EMAILS»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«IDENTITY»` from the regex capture group — the portion of `«SA_EMAIL»` between `${RBCC_account_retriever}-` and `@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}`
... {rbbc_call}
{buf_write_fact_multi}
with three positional arguments:
.... `<file_root>`: `«IDENTITY»` (bare identity — the basename root for the emitted fact file)
.... `<ext>`: `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_retriever` (resolves at source time to `roster-retriever`)
.... `<value>`: `«SA_EMAIL»` (the full service account email address)

//axhos_step
. *Display Summary*:
.. {rbbc_show}
count of emitted facts; no per-account stdout enumeration

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
by enumerating and deleting every package beneath the ark's
hallmark subtree via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a set of packages rooted at
`{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/` and distinguished by basename.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(basename `image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(basename `about`) contains SBOM and build metadata.
The
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
(basename `vouch`) contains verification results.
The
{rbtga_ark_pouch}
(basename `pouch`) contains the build context (conjure/bind only, absent for graft).
A fifth basename, `diags`, is present for conjure arks only (build-time diagnostics forwarded to the about pipeline).
For conjure vessels, a single `attest` package holds per-platform tags (`attest:«HALLMARK»-«ARCH»`).
Abjuring an ark deletes every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument (retained for AAK signature compatibility; not used to construct the subtree path, drops in AAL)
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if hallmark missing: "Hallmark parameter required"

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Validate Hallmark Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` matches pattern `[cbg]\d{12}-r\d{12}` (mode prefix + dual timestamp)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Hallmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
